main event: A civilian pilot reported seeing a whitish blue object traveling northeast and apparently descending at high speed.
interesting points: The object had no visible lights or markings.
The pilot did not think the object was a meteor.
The weather conditions were clear with good visibility.
The wind speeds were reported at the surface, 3,000 feet, 6,000 feet, and 10,000 feet.
The report mentions air scoop readings showing wind speeds between 27-34 knots and an altitude of 23-44 feet.
